==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Submersion
<hw>Sub*mer"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>submersio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>submersion</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of submerging, or putting under water or other fluid, or of
causing to be overflowed; the act of plunging under water, or of
drowning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being put under water or other fluid,
or of being overflowed or drowned.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Submetallic</ent>⟦br⟧
